<CHAPTER LBL="2"><TITLE><XREFTARGET ID="16790">Preparing for Installation</TITLE><PARAGRAPH>This chapter explains what to do to prepare for diskless software installation. It describes what to have on hand for the installation, what to evaluate and change to get ready for the diskless service, and how to organize the server filesystem that will contain the diskless software. It also provides an overview of diskless software and the installation procedure.</PARAGRAPH>
<PARAGRAPH>This chapter contains the following sections:</PARAGRAPH>
<BULLETLIST><BULLET><PARAGRAPH><XREF IDREF="31405" TYPE="TITLE">&ldquo;Obtaining a Software Distribution&rdquo;</XREF></PARAGRAPH>
</BULLET>
<BULLET><PARAGRAPH><XREF IDREF="37539" TYPE="TITLE">&ldquo;Checking a Server&rdquo;</XREF></PARAGRAPH>
</BULLET>
